The property of vector projection states that for any scalar $c$, 
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} (c \mathbf{v}) = c \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v}.\]
We are given that 
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}.\]Using the property of vector projection, we can compute $\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} (5 \mathbf{v})$ as follows:
